2. In this Act, except where the context otherwise requires -
"adjoining territory" means Tanzania and Uganda;
"offence" means an offence for which surrender to an adjoining territory can be made under the Extradition (Contiguous and Foreign Countries) Act;
"offender" means a person who has committed, or is reasonably suspected of having committed, an offence in an adjoining territory;
"police of an adjoining territory" means any uniformed member of the police force established by law in the adjoining territory and any person having powers of arrest derived from a tribal or other native authority in that adjoining territory and wearing a uniform, badge or other mark rendering him easily recognizable as an officer of that authority.
